article.description: Destin Barnes hit five 3-pointers and posted 17 points and Jacksonville beat Presbyterian 81-58 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Jacksonville works over Presbyterian 81-58
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Destin Barnes hit five 3-pointers and posted 17 points and Jacksonville beat Presbyterian 81-58 on Wednesday night. Mo Arnold had 14 points for Jacksonville (7-6). DeAnthony McCallum added 13 points. Chris Martin had 19 points for the Blue Hose (2-9). Cory Hightower added 11 points. Jacksonville matches up against Clemson on the road on Friday. Presbyterian plays Michigan on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
